# Current Projects

## 1. Object-Oriented Data-Processing Engine

This project implements a configurable processing framework using classes and independent processing modules.

The framework may process:

* sensor samples;
* measurement data;
* communication data;
* signal samples;
* recorded test data.

The software is divided into modules for:

* input acquisition;
* validation;
* preprocessing;
* filtering;
* numerical processing;
* statistical analysis;
* threshold detection;
* result generation;
* output storage;
* runtime configuration.

### Processing Flow

```text
Input Source
     |
     v
Data Validator
     |
     v
Preprocessing Stage
     |
     v
Processing Pipeline
     |
     v
Result Analyzer
     |
     v
Output Writer
```

### Example Processing Interface

```cpp
class ProcessingStage
{
public:
    virtual ~ProcessingStage() = default;

    virtual void process(
        std::vector<double>& samples
    ) = 0;

    [[nodiscard]]
    virtual std::string name() const = 0;
};
```

### Example Pipeline

```cpp
class ProcessingPipeline
{
public:
    void addStage(
        std::unique_ptr<ProcessingStage> stage
    );

    void execute(
        std::vector<double>& samples
    );

private:
    std::vector<
        std::unique_ptr<ProcessingStage>
    > stages_;
};
```

### Technical Concepts

* abstract interfaces;
* runtime polymorphism;
* class composition;
* smart pointers;
* RAII;
* dependency injection;
* reusable processing blocks;
* configurable software pipelines;
* unit-testable classes.

## 2. Template-Based Data-Structure Library

This project implements reusable data structures using C++ templates.

The library may include:

* fixed-capacity arrays;
* dynamic arrays;
* stacks;
* queues;
* circular buffers;
* priority queues;
* linked lists;
* binary trees;
* hash tables;
* fixed-capacity containers.

### Example Static Stack

```cpp
template<typename T, std::size_t Capacity>
class StaticStack
{
public:
    bool push(const T& value);

    bool push(T&& value);

    bool pop(T& value);

    [[nodiscard]]
    bool empty() const noexcept;

    [[nodiscard]]
    bool full() const noexcept;

    [[nodiscard]]
    std::size_t size() const noexcept;

private:
    std::array<T, Capacity> storage_{};
    std::size_t size_{0};
};
```

### Technical Concepts

* class templates;
* function templates;
* type safety;
* compile-time capacity;
* move-aware insertion;
* iterator support;
* reusable containers;
* complexity analysis;
* exception guarantees.

## 3. Event-Driven State Machine

This project implements a reusable state-machine framework for embedded controllers, device management, protocol handling, and fault recovery.

The implementation separates:

* states;
* events;
* transition rules;
* entry actions;
* exit actions;
* timeout processing;
* error states;
* recovery logic.

### Example States

```cpp
enum class SystemState
{
    Reset,
    Initializing,
    Idle,
    Active,
    Recovery,
    Fault
};
```

### Example Events

```cpp
enum class SystemEvent
{
    Start,
    Stop,
    DataReady,
    Timeout,
    Error,
    Reset
};
```

### Example State Interface

```cpp
class StateHandler
{
public:
    virtual ~StateHandler() = default;

    virtual SystemState handle(
        SystemEvent event
    ) = 0;

    virtual void onEntry()
    {
    }

    virtual void onExit()
    {
    }
};
```

### Technical Concepts

* strongly typed enumerations;
* state pattern;
* transition tables;
* event queues;
* polymorphic state handlers;
* timeout handling;
* invalid-transition detection;
* fault recovery;
* deterministic state changes.

## 4. Thread-Safe Circular Buffer

This project implements a circular buffer for transferring streaming data between threads or processing modules.

Possible applications include:

* UART buffering;
* ADC sample storage;
* audio streaming;
* network-packet buffering;
* DSP sample transfer;
* sensor-data acquisition;
* producer-consumer communication.

### Example Interface

```cpp
template<typename T>
class CircularBuffer
{
public:
    explicit CircularBuffer(
        std::size_t capacity
    );

    bool push(const T& value);

    bool push(T&& value);

    bool pop(T& value);

    [[nodiscard]]
    bool empty() const;

    [[nodiscard]]
    bool full() const;

    [[nodiscard]]
    std::size_t size() const;

private:
    std::vector<T> storage_;
    std::size_t head_{0};
    std::size_t tail_{0};
    std::size_t count_{0};

    mutable std::mutex mutex_;
};
```

### Technical Concepts

* producer-consumer communication;
* template-based storage;
* mutex synchronization;
* condition variables;
* move semantics;
* overflow policies;
* fixed-capacity buffering;
* latency measurement;
* throughput measurement.

