# Planned Projects

## 7. Fixed-Point DSP Library

This project will implement reusable signal-processing algorithms using fixed-point arithmetic.

The library may contain:

* Q15 arithmetic;
* Q31 arithmetic;
* saturating addition and subtraction;
* fixed-point multiplication;
* rounding;
* scaling;
* FIR filters;
* IIR filters;
* FFT processing;
* complex arithmetic;
* magnitude calculations;
* signal-power calculations;
* automatic gain scaling.

### Q15 Representation

A floating-point value can be converted to Q15 using:

[
x_{\mathrm{Q15}}
================

\operatorname{round}
\left(
x \times 2^{15}
\right)
]

The approximate floating-point value is recovered using:

[
x
\approx
\frac{x_{\mathrm{Q15}}}{2^{15}}
]

### Example Q15 Class

```cpp
class Q15
{
public:
    Q15() = default;

    explicit Q15(float value);

    static Q15 fromRaw(
        std::int16_t value
    );

    [[nodiscard]]
    float toFloat() const;

    [[nodiscard]]
    std::int16_t raw() const noexcept;

    Q15 operator+(const Q15& other) const;

    Q15 operator-(const Q15& other) const;

    Q15 operator*(const Q15& other) const;

private:
    std::int16_t value_{0};
};
```

### Technical Focus

* bit-accurate arithmetic;
* saturation handling;
* quantization-noise analysis;
* coefficient scaling;
* overflow protection;
* floating-point comparison;
* signal-to-quantization-noise ratio;
* execution-cycle measurement;
* memory optimization;
* SIMD-ready interfaces.

