## 9. Custom Memory Pool

This project will implement a fixed-capacity object pool for predictable memory allocation.

The allocator may support:

* fixed-size blocks;
* multiple object types;
* object construction;
* object destruction;
* free-list management;
* alignment handling;
* allocation statistics;
* invalid-release detection;
* corruption guards;
* optional thread safety.

### Example Object Pool

```cpp
template<typename T, std::size_t Capacity>
class ObjectPool
{
public:
    template<typename... Args>
    T* create(Args&&... args);

    bool destroy(T* object);

    [[nodiscard]]
    std::size_t available() const noexcept;

    [[nodiscard]]
    std::size_t used() const noexcept;

private:
    alignas(T)
    std::array<
        std::byte,
        sizeof(T) * Capacity
    > storage_{};

    std::array<bool, Capacity> occupied_{};
};
```

### Technical Focus

* placement construction;
* object-lifetime management;
* aligned storage;
* deterministic allocation;
* fragmentation avoidance;
* exception-safe object construction;
* allocation-latency measurement;
* allocator integration.

