## 11. Binary Protocol Framework

This project will implement a parser and encoder for a framed binary communication protocol.

### Example Frame

```text
+------------+--------+------+---------+----------+
| Start Byte | Length | Type | Payload | CRC      |
+------------+--------+------+---------+----------+
```

The parser will accept a continuous byte stream and preserve its state between calls.

### Parser States

* synchronization search;
* header reception;
* length validation;
* payload reception;
* CRC reception;
* frame validation;
* error recovery.

### Example Message Type

```cpp
struct ProtocolMessage
{
    std::uint8_t type{0};

    std::vector<std::uint8_t> payload;

    std::uint16_t crc{0};
};
```

### Technical Focus

* streaming parsing;
* partial-frame handling;
* malformed-frame recovery;
* synchronization recovery;
* CRC validation;
* buffer protection;
* protocol versioning;
* fuzz testing;
* invalid-input handling.

## 12. Lock-Free SPSC Queue

This project will implement a single-producer, single-consumer queue using atomic operations.

Possible applications include:

* DSP sample transfer;
* thread-to-thread communication;
* high-rate data acquisition;
* real-time logging;
* communication-event queues.

### Example Structure

```cpp
template<typename T, std::size_t Capacity>
class SpscQueue
{
public:
    bool push(const T& value);

    bool push(T&& value);

    bool pop(T& value);

    [[nodiscard]]
    bool empty() const noexcept;

private:
    alignas(64)
    std::atomic<std::size_t> head_{0};

    alignas(64)
    std::atomic<std::size_t> tail_{0};

    std::array<T, Capacity> storage_{};
};
```

### Technical Focus

* acquire and release memory ordering;
* atomic index management;
* cache-line alignment;
* false-sharing prevention;
* index wraparound;
* lock-free correctness;
* stress testing;
* latency and throughput comparison.

